Enum Class ReconcileAction

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<ReconcileAction>
org.nasdanika.exec.resources.ReconcileAction
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<ReconcileAction>, Constable, org.eclipse.emf.common.util.Enumerator
public enum ReconcileAction extends Enum<ReconcileAction> implements org.eclipse.emf.common.util.Enumerator
A representation of the literals of the enumeration 'Reconcile Action', and utility methods for working with them. Defines an action to take when a resource with the same name already exists.

  • Enum Constant Details

    • APPEND

      public static final ReconcileAction APPEND
      The 'Append' literal object. Appends new content to the existing content. For containers it means that new resources will be placed in the container next to the existing resources. For files it means that the new content will be appended after the existing content.
      See Also:
      • APPEND_VALUE

    • CANCEL

      public static final ReconcileAction CANCEL
      The 'Cancel' literal object. Cancels execution if resource already exists.
      See Also:
      • CANCEL_VALUE

    • KEEP

      public static final ReconcileAction KEEP
      The 'Keep' literal object. Keeps the existing resource intact.
      See Also:
      • KEEP_VALUE

    • MERGE

      public static final ReconcileAction MERGE
      The 'Merge' literal object. Merges old and new content of a file using a built-in or provided ``org.nasdanika.common.resources.Merger``. Merger is obtained from ``merger`` reference. For containers Merge is the same as Append.
      See Also:
      • MERGE_VALUE

    • OVERWRITE

      public static final ReconcileAction OVERWRITE
      The 'Overwrite' literal object. Overwrites existing resource. For containers - deletes their contents.
      See Also:
      • OVERWRITE_VALUE
